"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-what-is-breaking-explaining-new-olympic-event-2024\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Paris Olympics are finally here, and with this year's Games comes a couple of new events.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 98, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 23}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's Games\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 68}, {\"ngram\": \"a couple\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 83}, {\"ngram\": \"new events\", \"from\": 87, \"to\": 97}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is kayak cross, a canoe slalom event debuting for the first time.\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.999883419084083, \"rank\": 0.00011659450880360429, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a canoe slalom event\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 141}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be a men's competition for artistic swimming, an Olympic first.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a men's competition\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 204}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic swimming\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But perhaps the most fascinating new event is breaking, which debuted at the Youth Olympic Games in 2018 and was successful enough to be introduced into the 2024 Paris games.\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 323, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.688803341533838e-13, \"text\": \"Youth Olympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.8235632070293587e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most fascinating new event\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As is the case when a new event is introduced into the Olympics (and even when it's not a new event), there is a good chance you are going to turn on the television and be presented with a sport you do not understand at all.\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"a new event\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 453}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 485}, {\"ngram\": \"a new event\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"a good chance\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"the television\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, in this space, we endeavor to inform you everything you need to know about the sport breaking and how to enjoy it.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this space\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In more casual terms, breaking is a more formalized version of break dancing.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more casual terms\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 787}, {\"ngram\": \"a more formalized version\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"break dancing\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Described by the Olympics website as an \\\"urban dance style\\\" with roots in hip-hop culture, it is probably very similar to what you are imagining\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a dance style with a low center of gravity involving plenty of twists, spins, and precise footwork while using every part of the body as leverage.\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics website\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\\"urban dance style\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"roots\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop culture\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"imagining\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a dance style\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"a low center\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1023}, {\"ngram\": \"gravity\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1034}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"twists\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"spins\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1068}, {\"ngram\": \"precise footwork\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"every part\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"the body\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"leverage\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike some of the more off-the-beaten-path Olympic sports, breaking will at least look familiar to the average American consumer due to its presence in pop culture.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999320009275078, \"rank\": 6.789083252411502e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"path\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"its presence\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"pop culture\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1304}]}, {\"sentence\": \"See: theStep Upmovie series.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theStep Upmovie series\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, what Channing Tatum was doing as Tyler Gage is a little different than what the athletes competing at the Olympics will do.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channing_Tatum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Channing Tatum\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channing_Tatum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channing_Tatum\"}, {\"begin\": 1380, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tyler\", \"score\": 0.9768317354466911, \"rank\": 0.023394111953709513, \"text\": \"Tyler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tyler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tyler\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So how, exactly, will breaking work in Paris?\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.8235632070293587e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be 32 participants in total\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\\u00c2 16 men and 16 women, called \\\"B-Boys\\\" and \\\"B-Girls.\\\"\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"32 participants\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"total\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1560}, {\"ngram\": \"16 men\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"16 women\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"B-Boys\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"B-Girls\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will face each other in one-on-one competitions in a round robin format to begin before moving to elimination-style leading into the medal match.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one-on-one competitions\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"a round robin format\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"elimination-style\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal match\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each \\\"battle\\\" consists of three one-minute performances for each contestant.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each \\\"battle\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"three one-minute performances\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1820}, {\"ngram\": \"each contestant\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The battle is over when one breaker wins two rounds.\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The battle\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"one breaker\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1877}, {\"ngram\": \"two rounds\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As explained by theOlympics website, \\\"Athletes will use a combination of power moves\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094including windmills, the 6-step, and freezes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094as they adapt their style and improvise to the beat of the DJ\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tracks in a bid to secure the judges\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 votes and take home the first Olympic breaking medals.\\\"\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 2190, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympics website\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"a combination\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 1973}, {\"ngram\": \"windmills\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2001}, {\"ngram\": \"their style\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"improvise\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2068}, {\"ngram\": \"the beat\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2080}, {\"ngram\": \"the DJ\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tracks\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"a bid\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2110}, {\"ngram\": \"the judges\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 votes\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympic breaking medals\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As suggested above, these will not be choreographed routines.\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"choreographed routines\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not figure skating, where every last movement is finalized months before the Olympics and the music is all customized for each routine.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2395, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"figure skating\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2278}, {\"ngram\": \"every last movement\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2305}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"the music\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"each routine\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2394}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breakers do not know what music will play when it's time to battle and instead must improvise based on what they hear.\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2514, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Breakers\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2404}, {\"ngram\": \"what music\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2427}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"battle\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2462}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is, therefore, not just a battle of dance, but a war of creativity, too.\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"not just a battle\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2550}, {\"ngram\": \"dance\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"a war\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2570}, {\"ngram\": \"creativity\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All that begs the natural next question\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 how does a breaker win?\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to NBC, breaking will feature a panel of nine judges.\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2673, \"end\": 2676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9585835204655214, \"rank\": 0.043172097462263005, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2686}, {\"ngram\": \"a panel\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2707}, {\"ngram\": \"nine judges\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will evaluate each performance based on six aspects of breaking: creativity, personality, technique, variety, performativity and musicality.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each performance\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"six aspects\", \"from\": 2769, \"to\": 2780}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2792}, {\"ngram\": \"creativity\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2804}, {\"ngram\": \"personality\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"technique\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2828}, {\"ngram\": \"variety\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"performativity\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2853}, {\"ngram\": \"musicality\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each category is not weighed equally, however.\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each category\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Performativity and creativity account for 60% of the scores, while the other four account for 40%.\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Performativity\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"creativity\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 2947}, {\"ngram\": \"60%\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2963}, {\"ngram\": \"the scores\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 2977}, {\"ngram\": \"40%\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As, effectively, a brand-new sport there is no famous breaker the world knows will come into Paris and dominate.\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3111, \"end\": 3116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.8235632070293587e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brand-new sport\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"no famous breaker\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3079}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It opens the door for someone to make a name for themselves and a mighty impression on the international community.\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3246, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the door\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3148}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3160}, {\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3175}, {\"ngram\": \"the international community\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3245}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the men's side, NBC lists Americans Victor Montalvo and Jeffery Louis as competitors to watch along with Canada's Philip Kim, Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Shigeyuki Nakarai, and France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Danis Civil.\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9585835204655214, \"rank\": 0.043172097462263005, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \